{"key":"processedPost-8612880","value":{"id":8612880,"first":8608146,"last":8615506,"when":1215627135,"utime":"07/09/08 09:12 PM","content":"I believe spore allergies are species specific.&nbsp; So far, I only have one species that I'm horribly allergic to, <i>H ulmarius</i>.&nbsp; In fact, I won't even grow that one indoors anymore.&nbsp; Once you get a heavy dose of spores and your immune system rejects them, you'll be allergic to that species' spores, even in very small amounts, perhaps forever.&nbsp; For cubes, the answer is to pick large pins prior to the veil beginning to tear.&nbsp; Besides, they're at peak quality at that time anyway. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\":wink:\"/><br />RR","title":"Re: Looking for releif from spore allergy"}}